# DocuMind AI — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a Next.js 14 App Router project. It is a RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)
platform using LangChain.js, OpenAI GPT-4o, Supabase pgvector, and Vercel.

---

## Stack — Always Use These, Never Suggest Alternatives
- Framework: Next.js 14 with App Router (not Pages Router)
- Styling: TailwindCSS only — no inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components
- AI: LangChain.js — not LlamaIndex, not Vercel AI SDK (unless asked)
- Vector DB: Supabase pgvector — not Pinecone, not Weaviate
- Storage + Auth: Supabase — not Firebase, not Clerk
- Language: JavaScript (.js / .jsx) — not TypeScript unless explicitly asked

---

## Next.js App Router Rules

- Default all components to Server Components unless they need interactivity
- Add `'use client'` only when using: useState, useEffect, useRef, event handlers, browser APIs
- API routes live in `app/api/**/route.js` — use named exports: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
- Use `next/navigation` (not `next/router`) for routing hooks
- Use `next/image` for all images
- Server components fetch data directly — no useEffect for data fetching
- Streaming responses use `new Response(readableStream)` in route handlers

## File & Folder Conventions
- Pages: `app/[route]/page.jsx`
- Layouts: `app/[route]/layout.jsx`
- API: `app/api/[route]/route.js`
- Reusable UI: `components/[ComponentName].jsx` (PascalCase)
- Utilities / lib: `lib/[name].js` (camelCase)
- Supabase client (browser): `lib/supabase.js`
- Supabase client (server): `lib/supabase-server.js`

---

## Supabase Rules

- Browser client (`lib/supabase.js`): uses `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- Server client (`lib/supabase-server.js`): uses `SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY` — server only
- NEVER import `supabase-server.js` in any client component or `'use client'` file
- NEVER expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY` to the browser
- Always handle Supabase errors: `const { data, error } = await supabase...` — check error
- RLS is enabled — always pass `user_id` when inserting user-upload documents

### Namespace Values (Hardcoded — Never Change)
- `'user-upload'` — user's own PDFs
- `'kb-hr'` — HR knowledge base
- `'kb-legal'` — Legal knowledge base
- `'kb-engineering'` — Engineering knowledge base

---

## LangChain.js Rules

- Import from specific subpaths: `'langchain/embeddings/openai'` not `'langchain'`
- Always use `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` with `chunkSize: 500, chunkOverlap: 50`
- Always use `text-embedding-3-small` for embeddings (1536 dimensions)
- Always use `gpt-4o` for generation — not gpt-3.5, not gpt-4-turbo
- For streaming: use `llm.stream()` and pipe to a `ReadableStream` in the route handler
- Always include `returnSourceDocuments: true` in QA chains for citations

---

## Code Style

- Use `const` over `let` wherever possible — never `var`
- Use async/await — not .then().catch() chains
- Always wrap async operations in try/catch in API routes
- Return consistent JSON error shape: `{ error: 'message' }` with appropriate HTTP status
- Use optional chaining: `data?.field` not `data && data.field`
- Destructure props at component top: `function Component({ prop1, prop2 }) {}`
- Export components as default: `export default function ComponentName() {}`
- Export utilities as named: `export async function myUtil() {}`

---

## TailwindCSS Rules

- Mobile-first responsive: base styles for mobile, `md:` and `lg:` for larger screens
- Use Tailwind's color palette — no custom hex values unless in `tailwind.config.js`
- For dark mode: use `dark:` prefix — document has `className="dark"` on root
- Common patterns to reuse:
  - Card: `rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm`
  - Button primary: `rounded-lg bg-blue-600 px-4 py-2 text-white hover:bg-blue-700`
  - Input: `rounded-lg border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500`

---

## AI / RAG Specific Rules

- Never return raw LLM output without source citations
- Always validate that `namespace` is one of the 4 allowed values before querying
- Chunk size decisions: 500 tokens per chunk, 50 overlap — do not change without reason
- Never store the full PDF in the database — only chunks + embeddings
- PDFs are stored in Supabase Storage bucket `pdfs` — embeddings in `documents` table
- Always include `metadata: { filename, page, source }` when inserting document chunks

---

## Security Rules

- Never log OpenAI API keys or Supabase service keys
- Validate all user input before passing to LangChain or Supabase
- File uploads: only accept `application/pdf` MIME type
- Max file size: 10MB per upload
- Always check `auth.uid()` in server routes before any database operation
- Admin routes (`/api/admin/*`) must verify admin role from Supabase user metadata

---

## What NOT to Do
- Do not use Pages Router (`pages/` directory)
- Do not use `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps`
- Do not use `axios` — use native `fetch`
- Do not use `moment.js` — use native `Date` or `date-fns`
- Do not install Pinecone, Firebase, or Clerk
- Do not add TypeScript config unless asked
- Do not use `useEffect` for data fetching in Server Components
- Do not cache the Supabase server client across requests
